These were photos taken by son, father, skateboarding enthusiast and aspiring photographer Tyre Nichols. He was trying to get home when five police officers who had sworn to protect and serve the people decided to use him as a human piñata; senselessly beating him to death while he cried out for his mother. What is wrong with us? Our country is ill. We must figure out how to get better as a society so no mother has to experience the agony that I know Tyre's mother must be in now. 💔 #policereform #tyrenichols

Like you, I feel gutted by the devastation and loss after Monday morning’s 7.8 magnitude earthquake that struck Turkey and Syria killing thousands and with many more wounded. At last count I read 7700dead, and the number will only go up.  Edit: death toll is now at 21,000. It's just unthinkable. Anything we can do to help with matter.  Even if it's giving food and blankets to one family. 
The impact of the earthquake will have a tremendous effect on the access to food for civilians. Many of whom are women and children and who depend on humanitarian assistance. 
 The U.N. World Food Programme has operated in Turkey and Syria for decades and will continue to provide unconditional food assistance to vulnerable groups during the disaster recovery and for months to come.

 Please join to help feed millions of vulnerable people. @WFPUSA @WFP @worldfoodprogramme There is a link in my bio. Any amount will help. #syria #turkey ##savelives

Please come join us for a special night of music, stories and connection featuring a true professional and talented artist, Molly Ringwald. Molly has supported me and my family since I met her and she has been helping with the development of my piece, Just Five Minutes. She is a beautiful person inside and out. We will be in Newtown, Connecticut at Edmond Town, Hall, on Saturday November 11,2023 featuring Jim Allen, Mary Birdsong, Kimberly Ann Evans, Howard Carlough, Niles Spaulding  and of course my incredible partner, David Cole Wheeler. I will be performing as well all to fundraise and support our 501C3, Ben’s Lighthouse. Molly Ringwald photo credit Willy Somma. Thank you to the Mazursky Foundation and Faxon Law for sponsoring this event! Please come and support us! #benslighthouse #edmondtownhall #alwaysforben

I'm really enjoying reading Barbra Streisand's memoir- or rather listening to her read it. What a life! Since it's nice and long, I'm taking little breaks to re-watch some of her films. I remember meeting Barbra when I was a teenager. My sister was working at A&M records when she was recording there. She was incredibly warm and friendly with me but I was a little too shy and didn't talk to her as much as I wish I had. Fact: If I could have anyone's nose, it would be hers.
